      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Kong request metrics are not used here. AWS dev uses Istio-only ingress; private-dev Kong is a separate migration scope. Istio monitoring follows one istiod target and one istio-ingressgateway target in istio-system, plus the exact nine sidecar app/namespace pairs: auth-service/dropmong-auth, user-service/dropmong-user, catalog-service/dropmong-catalog, coupon-service/dropmong-coupon, interest-service/dropmong-interest, order-service/dropmong-order, payment-service/dropmong-payment, notification-service/dropmong-notification, and dropmong-web/dropmong-web. Coupon stays in static coverage; its known runtime waiver means Task 6 remains partial until the owner recovers it. Request IDs belong in x-request-id headers and structured logs, never metric labels."
      },
      "id": 1,
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 3
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Istiod Scrape Targets",
      "type": "stat",
      "description": null,
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus"
          },
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "sum by (namespace, pod) (up{namespace=\"istio-system\",pod=~\"istiod-.*\"})",
          "legendFormat": "{{namespace}}/{{pod}}",
          "range": true,
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "links": [

      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
